{{Infobox Organization | name = I.I.I.&nbsp;– Insurance Information Institute | image = | size = | caption = | abbreviation = I.I.I. | motto = | formation = {{start date and age|1959|p=yes}} | extinction = | type = Industry association | status = [[Nonprofit organization]] (since 1989) | purpose = To improve public understanding of insurance | location = New York, NY | membership = |membership_year = | leader_title = President and Chief Executive Officer | leader_name = Sean Kevelighan | main_organ = |revenue = $9,545,189<ref name="ProPublica"/> |revenue_year = 2015 |expenses = $8,406,962<ref name="ProPublica"/> |expenses_year = 2015 | website = {{URL|http://iii.org/}} }}
The '''Insurance Information Institute''' ("I.I.I.") is a [[United States|U.S.]] [[Trade association|industry association]] which exists "to improve public understanding of [[insurance]]&nbsp;&ndash; what it does and how it works."<ref>{{cite web | title = About Us |publisher = Insurance Information Institute. iii.org | url = https://www.iii.org/about-us | accessdate = 2017-10-21 }}</ref> Founded in 1959, the organization is based in [[New York City]].<ref>"[https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapid=104483485 Company Overview of Insurance Information Institute, Inc.]". [[Bloomberg L.P.|Bloomberg]]. Bloomberg.com. Retrieved 2017-10-21.</ref> Since 1989 the I.I.I. has held [[501(c) organization#501(c)(6)|501(c)(6)]] tax-exempt status (defined as business leagues, chambers of commerce, boards of trade, and the like).<ref name="ProPublica">"[https://projects.propublica.org/nonprofits/organizations/131912455 Insurance Information Institute Inc.]" (Nonprofit Explorer profile). [[ProPublica]]. propublica.org. Retrieved 2017-10-21.</ref>
The I.I.I. web site provides information for consumers, the media, researchers and the general public on a wide range of topics, including [[Vehicle insurance|automobile insurance]], [[Home insurance|homeowner's insurance]], [[life insurance]], [[life annuity|annuities]], [[health insurance]], [[long-term care insurance]] and [[disability insurance]]. The Web site also contains papers, presentations and factsheets that focus on financial results, [[Disaster|disasters]], [[climate change]], and other key issues the insurance industry faces. In addition, a number of publications can be purchased via the I.I.I. store, including the ''Insurance Fact Book'', the ''Financial Services Fact Book'', ''Insuring Your Business'', the ''Insurance Handbook'' and a wide variety of brochures, including "12 Ways to Lower Your Homeowners Insurance Costs".<ref>"[https://www.iii.org/press-release/iii-launches-new-online-bookstore-022008 I.I.I. Launches New Online Bookstore]" (press release). Insurance Information Institute. iii.org. February&nbsp;20, 2008. Retrieved 2017-10-21.</ref>
The institute's current president and chief executive officer, Sean Kevelighan, assumed the post in August 2016.<ref>"[https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=379295636&privcapId=104483485 Sean Kevelighan]" (executive profile). Bloomberg. Bloomberg.com. Retrieved 2017-10-21.</ref> Kevelighan succeeded Robert Hartwig, who had led I.I.I. since 2007; Hartwig left in order to become a faculty member in the University of South Carolina’s [[Darla Moore School of Business]], and director of the school's Risk and Uncertainty Management Center.<ref>Donlon, Rosalie L. (July&nbsp;13, 2016). "[http://www.propertycasualty360.com/2016/07/13/insurance-information-institute-names-sean-kevelig Insurance Information Institute names Sean Kevelighan president and CEO]". Property Casualty 360 &#176;. propertycasualty.com. Retrieved 2017-10-21.</ref>
